# Security Standards

## API Key Protection (CRITICAL)

You must NEVER include API keys in:
- Frontend code
- HTTP responses
- Logs
- Git commits
- Error messages

You must:
- Store API keys in environment variables only (${SPOONACULAR_API_KEY})
- Use API keys only in backend service layer
- Ensure frontend calls backend only, never external APIs directly

Ensure Git protection:
- .env in .gitignore
- .env.example committed with placeholders only

## Dependencies

You must:
- Enable automated scanning (Dependabot)
- Check for updates weekly
- Apply security patches immediately
- Run: ./gradlew dependencyCheckAnalyze (backend), npm audit (frontend)
